problem: What integer is closest to the value of $\sqrt[3]{6^3+8^3}$?
solution: We have $\sqrt[3]{6^3 + 8^3} = \sqrt[3]{216 + 512} = \sqrt[3]{728}$. To find the integer closest to this, we note that $8^3 = 512$, $9^3= 729$, and $10^3 =1000$, so $\sqrt[3]{728}$ is very close to $\boxed{9}$.
chatgpt_solution:
We have  \begin{align*}
\sqrt[3]{6^3+8^3}&=\sqrt[3]{216+512}\\
&=\sqrt[3]{728}.
\end{align*} The prime factorization of 728 is $2^3\cdot 7 \cdot 13$. The prime factorization of a perfect cube must have exponents that are multiples of 3. There are 2 choices: $2^0\cdot 7^0\cdot 13^0=1$, and $2^3\cdot 7^3 \cdot 13^3=2002$. Since 728 is closer to 2002 than it is to 1, $\sqrt[3]{728}$ is closer to $\boxed{12}$.
